Class
Description
AbstractType
This is a utility class that handles common code for implementations of TypeConcrete, including holding a reference to a TypeSystem and redirecting Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() to TypeConcrete.equalsExactly(TypeConcrete) and TypeConcrete.hashCodeExactly().
AbstractTypeResolver<T,K>
This is a utility class that handles common code for implementations of TypeResolver, including holding a reference to the TypeSystem and a TypeCache, as well as providing default implementations of TypeResolver.acceptsType(Object) and TypeResolver.acceptsDeclaration(Object).
AbstractTypeSolver
This is a utility class that provides some common code for implementations of TypeSolver, such as holding a reference to the relevant TypeSystem, and a list of accepted TypeConstraint types.

This interface represents any type in the Java type system.

This class represents an array type.

Represents a cache of Types used by a TypeResolver.
TypeConcrete
This interface represents a Type in the Java type system which is not a declaration.
TypeConstraint
This interface represents some sort of constraint over Types, for use in TypeSolvers.

Represents a TypeConcrete that requires subtype is assignable to parent.
